1
00:00:00,874 --> 00:00:02,539
Previously on "One Tree Hill"...

2
00:00:02,555 --> 00:00:05,438
My name is Elizabeth. I'm your mother.

3
00:00:05,919 --> 00:00:07,244
Is this woman my mother?

4
00:00:07,311 --> 00:00:09,682
Your mom is gone, Peyton.

5
00:00:09,748 --> 00:00:13,020
But your biological mother is alive.

6
00:00:13,251 --> 00:00:14,566
Are you and Haley fighting?

7
00:00:14,643 --> 00:00:18,070
My problem is with anybody who just vanishes and then waltzes back in

8
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:20,250
and expects to be instantly forgiven.

9
00:00:20,316 --> 00:00:24,443
You know, we could totally have a summer-like fling, just in the fall.

10
00:00:24,510 --> 00:00:27,142
And non-exclusive.

11
00:00:28,481 --> 00:00:30,939
There wasn't a moment when I was away

12
00:00:31,271 --> 00:00:33,387
that my heart wasn't with you in Tree Hill.

13
00:00:33,456 --> 00:00:34,598
I'm going to High Flyers.

14
00:00:34,664 --> 00:00:37,131
Unlike you, I'm taking my heart with me.

15
00:00:37,889 --> 00:00:39,199
We're not brothers.

16
00:00:39,532 --> 00:00:40,797
We're not even friends.

17
00:00:40,884 --> 00:00:43,168
Three months ago, someone tried to kill me.

18
00:00:43,398 --> 00:00:46,639
And when I find out who did this to me -- and I will find out soon --

19
00:00:46,727 --> 00:00:49,635
the sins I commit then could turn this place to rubble.

20
00:01:07,472 --> 00:01:09,879
Henry David Thoreau once wrote,

21
00:01:09,987 --> 00:01:12,163
"Live each season as it passes.

22
00:01:12,265 --> 00:01:16,371
Breathe the air, drink the drink, taste the fruit,

23
00:01:16,706 --> 00:01:20,252
and resign yourself to the influences of each."

24
00:01:20,708 --> 00:01:23,053
Well, well. Look who's starting a fire.

25
00:01:45,699 --> 00:01:46,861
Rise and shine.

26
00:01:47,117 --> 00:01:48,295
Nice of you to knock.

27
00:01:48,366 --> 00:01:50,604
I didn't want to wake you, sleeping bitchy.

28
00:01:50,677 --> 00:01:52,498
Besides, I had to get the list ready.

29
00:01:52,565 --> 00:01:53,589
What list?

30
00:01:53,769 --> 00:01:54,772
This list.

31
00:01:57,087 --> 00:01:58,944
What is that exactly?

32
00:01:59,656 --> 00:02:02,550
Since you and I are both officially available again

33
00:02:02,601 --> 00:02:04,807
and tonight is the end-of-summer beach party -- which means

34
00:02:04,863 --> 00:02:06,886
partial, if not total, naked nudity --

35
00:02:06,946 --> 00:02:10,274
I have made a list of all of the available guys,

36
00:02:10,346 --> 00:02:13,454
so that we can avoid the pain and hardship of another Lucas love triangle.

37
00:02:13,526 --> 00:02:17,307
You mean the Lucas that you're supposedly dating?

38
00:02:18,344 --> 00:02:20,260
Okay, I'm sorry. I didn't get any of that.

39
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:23,173
Did you just say something about me puking at a rave?

40
00:02:23,803 --> 00:02:27,555
I said, "the Lucas you're supposedly dating."

41
00:02:27,617 --> 00:02:28,893
Non-exclusively.

42
00:02:28,959 --> 00:02:30,480
- Huh.
- What "huh"?

43
00:02:30,535 --> 00:02:32,199
I have dated multiple guys before.

44
00:02:32,276 --> 00:02:33,429
Yeah, I know.

45
00:02:33,490 --> 00:02:37,692
In fact, you are the queen of the multiple-boy dating scenario.

46
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:40,146
I'm just surprised you're doing it with Lucas.

47
00:02:40,177 --> 00:02:43,786
You know what they say. When it comes to boys, I'm full of surprises.

48
00:02:43,848 --> 00:02:45,649
But I thought you were the new, responsible Brooke.

49
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:51,042
Uh, so last season. Responsible Brooke is good, but party Brooke is gooder.

50
00:02:51,063 --> 00:02:51,927
Check it out.

51
00:02:51,999 --> 00:02:55,250
I get Lucas, Mouth, half the guys on the team --

52
00:02:55,306 --> 00:02:57,543
I put my first choices here, but we can totally mix and match.

53
00:02:57,611 --> 00:03:01,398
Any and all lifeguards, Nathan's uncle Cooper -- so hot -- Larry.

54
00:03:01,450 --> 00:03:04,850
Whoa! Larry like my dad Larry?

55
00:03:05,029 --> 00:03:07,707
Of course! He's my hot-dad fantasy.

56
00:03:08,290 --> 00:03:11,147
Peyton, he is a total dilf.

57
00:03:11,210 --> 00:03:13,094
And, besides, I gave you Dan.

58
00:03:13,943 --> 00:03:16,186
And I get Dave Grohl from the Foo Fighters.

59
00:03:17,737 --> 00:03:21,332
You get Jake, as promised, Nathan -- but he comes with an asterisk,

60
00:03:21,377 --> 00:03:24,716
because nobody knows what is going on with him and Haley in high school married limbo.

61
00:03:24,765 --> 00:03:26,896
The other half of the guys on the team, Anna --

62
00:03:26,948 --> 00:03:30,839
because, well, you never know, and she was totally into you.

63
00:03:30,896 --> 00:03:33,708
And all the river court boys -- Skills, Fergie, and Garbage.

64
00:03:34,224 --> 00:03:35,089
Junk.

65
00:03:35,937 --> 00:03:36,764
Right.

66
00:03:37,070 --> 00:03:38,873
And, finally, the rest of the Foo Fighters.

67
00:03:38,970 --> 00:03:41,223
Why do you get Dave Grohl? I want Dave Grohl.

68
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:42,013
No way.

69
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:44,121
So I get a fugitive and a married guy.

70
00:03:46,763 --> 00:03:49,646
Fine. You take Dave Grohl. I'm taking Anna.

71
00:03:49,707 --> 00:03:50,869
- Deal.
- Deal.

72
00:03:50,936 --> 00:03:52,789
Okay. Nighty-night. Thanks. Bye.

73
00:04:05,409 --> 00:04:06,496
You're back.

74
00:04:07,944 --> 00:04:08,763
Maybe.

75
00:04:09,521 --> 00:04:11,360
Maybe you're just high and seeing things.

76
00:04:12,608 --> 00:04:16,291
So I guess you're still pissed at me, which, personally, I think is crap.

77
00:04:16,362 --> 00:04:17,381
But you tell me.

78
00:04:17,523 --> 00:04:18,519
Are we friends?

79
00:04:19,414 --> 00:04:20,283
I'll tell you what.

80
00:04:20,540 --> 00:04:22,885
I'll play you for it -- game to 11.

81
00:04:23,629 --> 00:04:24,687
Make it, take it...

82
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,288
for our friendship.

83
00:05:23,432 --> 00:05:24,315
Game.

84
00:05:27,778 --> 00:05:28,743
Where are you going?

85
00:05:29,036 --> 00:05:29,839
You lost.

86
00:05:30,592 --> 00:05:32,322
I guess that means we're still not friends.

87
00:06:32,536 --> 00:06:34,782
Hiya, new roommate. Getting all moved in?

88
00:06:35,079 --> 00:06:38,393
Uh, with the six feet that you gave me? Yeah. Sure.

89
00:06:38,453 --> 00:06:39,155
Good.

90
00:06:39,421 --> 00:06:40,229
Thank you.

91
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,217
Hey,  great idea.

92
00:06:42,709 --> 00:06:43,485
What?

93
00:06:43,605 --> 00:06:46,997
Wearing your wedding ring -- it's like a total aphrodisiac for some guys.

94
00:06:47,654 --> 00:06:50,229
I just need it to be an aphrodisiac for one guy.

95
00:06:50,306 --> 00:06:51,725
Why? Do you have a new guy?

96
00:06:52,994 --> 00:06:54,560
For Nathan, Brooke.

97
00:06:56,933 --> 00:07:01,115
Hmm, I see. About him -- I notice you haven't unpacked.

98
00:07:01,248 --> 00:07:02,844
A little naive, don't you think?

99
00:07:02,913 --> 00:07:05,738
No. No, I'm just stalling.

100
00:07:05,811 --> 00:07:10,992
I mean, it's like if I unpack, my split with Nathan will be more real.

101
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:13,727
I hate to say it, but it's real enough already.

102
00:07:13,966 --> 00:07:15,451
Yeah, I know.

103
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:20,051
Okay. No, no, none of that.

104
00:07:20,116 --> 00:07:21,733
Come here. I have a surprise for you.

105
00:07:21,815 --> 00:07:23,208
Come on, come on. This will be fun.

106
00:07:24,381 --> 00:07:26,895
This is totally gonna cheer you up.

107
00:07:30,009 --> 00:07:30,955
Whoa!

108
00:07:31,614 --> 00:07:35,840
Wha-- this is amazing. When did you do this?

109
00:07:35,911 --> 00:07:37,340
Last night, while you were sleeping.

110
00:07:37,656 --> 00:07:40,289
You totally sleep like a dead person.

111
00:07:40,531 --> 00:07:41,420
Shut up.

112
00:07:41,974 --> 00:07:43,392
This looks awesome.

113
00:07:43,519 --> 00:07:44,375
Thanks.

114
00:07:45,304 --> 00:07:48,896
By the way, I'm kind of gonna need to ask for next month's rent now,

115
00:07:48,942 --> 00:07:53,226
'cause I sort of spent this month's rent on the couch and the rugs and things.

116
00:07:53,584 --> 00:07:56,688
Okay, although you really shouldn't have to pay for this stuff yourself.

117
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:58,517
We're roommates now. I'll go half.

118
00:07:58,578 --> 00:07:59,586
- Really?
- Yeah.

119
00:07:59,647 --> 00:08:02,437
I  was hoping you'd say that, 'cause I kind of ate half your rainbow sherbet

120
00:08:02,442 --> 00:08:04,506
last night while I was hanging the wall mural.

121
00:08:04,963 --> 00:08:06,171
Where'd you get it, anyway?

122
00:08:06,241 --> 00:08:07,250
The freezer?

123
00:08:07,476 --> 00:08:08,439
The wall mural.

124
00:08:08,561 --> 00:08:11,389
Oh, Peyton made it for me. It's the french riviera.

125
00:08:11,444 --> 00:08:13,877
Gosh, I haven't talked to Peyton in, like, forever.

126
00:08:13,932 --> 00:08:16,877
Lucas filled me in on her mom situation. What the heck?

127
00:08:16,984 --> 00:08:21,613
Yeah, the mom situation's on high alert right now 'cause Ellie's back in town.

128
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:23,130
How's Peyton taking it?

129
00:08:23,508 --> 00:08:24,449
Well...

130
00:08:25,407 --> 00:08:26,747
There she is now.

131
00:08:26,851 --> 00:08:29,404
She's sending me a last-minute flyer for the party tonight.

132
00:08:29,514 --> 00:08:32,794
Speaking of which, you are not allowed to sulk tonight.

133
00:08:32,866 --> 00:08:33,937
I don't sulk.

134
00:08:34,003 --> 00:08:35,822
You sulk. You're a sulker.

135
00:08:35,903 --> 00:08:39,102
But tonight, you're gonna have fun. After all, it's a party.

136
00:08:39,164 --> 00:08:42,538
It's supposed to be... dark and depressing?

137
00:08:42,893 --> 00:08:46,066
Well, you asked how she's taking it. There you go.

138
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:09,876
Hi, Peyton.

139
00:09:09,990 --> 00:09:12,853
Last time I saw you, you were slamming a door in my face.

140
00:09:12,935 --> 00:09:14,062
So let's have it.

141
00:09:14,456 --> 00:09:15,504
What's that?

142
00:09:15,864 --> 00:09:20,692
The heart wrenching, yet inspirational tale of a young girl's complex decision

143
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:23,545
to part with the daughter she desperately loves.

144
00:09:23,761 --> 00:09:25,569
Actually, it's not that complex.

145
00:09:26,041 --> 00:09:29,307
At the time I got pregnant, I liked drugs more than I liked you.

146
00:09:29,376 --> 00:09:30,348
That's it.

147
00:09:34,952 --> 00:09:36,908
I'm a different person now, Peyton.

148
00:09:37,497 --> 00:09:40,964
But those decisions are still mine. I can't change that.

149
00:09:41,036 --> 00:09:45,688
And what? So you -- you're just coming to make peace with yourself?

150
00:09:46,708 --> 00:09:48,193
That is so screwed up.

151
00:09:48,255 --> 00:09:51,126
You can't just crawl out of your hole after 17 years

152
00:09:51,182 --> 00:09:53,439
and cause a plague like some kind of locust.

153
00:09:53,517 --> 00:09:56,677
For what it's worth, I crawled out of my hole a long time ago.

154
00:09:58,767 --> 00:10:00,624
Your father wouldn't let me see you.

155
00:10:02,585 --> 00:10:03,958
I don't believe you.

156
00:10:06,271 --> 00:10:09,754
You used to sit under a bridge by the river...

157
00:10:11,171 --> 00:10:16,133
you and a brunette girl who wore a little too much eye makeup for a 10-year-old.

158
00:10:22,057 --> 00:10:23,884
She tried to see me...

159
00:10:24,611 --> 00:10:26,931
like seven years ago, but you sent her away!

160
00:10:26,952 --> 00:10:27,888
That's right.

161
00:10:28,441 --> 00:10:29,752
How could you do that?

162
00:10:29,809 --> 00:10:32,221
Because I'm your dad and it was my call.

163
00:10:32,388 --> 00:10:33,874
Unbelievable.

164
00:10:34,103 --> 00:10:35,169
- Peyton.
- Forget it!

165
00:10:35,225 --> 00:10:36,058
Peyton!

166
00:10:41,631 --> 00:10:42,496
Hey!

167
00:10:42,582 --> 00:10:45,352
I understand you're upset. But don't be slamming doors

168
00:10:45,425 --> 00:10:47,625
and stomping your little chicken ass around this house

169
00:10:47,677 --> 00:10:49,843
while I'm talking with you. I am still your father.

170
00:10:49,894 --> 00:10:52,531
But you're not my father, are you?

171
00:10:58,809 --> 00:11:02,475
When Ellie gave you up, she agreed not to see you.

172
00:11:02,524 --> 00:11:05,647
Had your mother lived, we would have told you. It would have been up to you.

173
00:11:05,704 --> 00:11:09,835
But when she died, I decided it would be too hard, too confusing for you.

174
00:11:09,843 --> 00:11:11,450
Maybe that was a mistake.

175
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:12,898
Maybe it was a mistake.

176
00:11:14,623 --> 00:11:18,120
You know what, dad? This -- this is you, okay?

177
00:11:19,226 --> 00:11:21,387
Kind of a broken record lately, don't you think?

178
00:11:25,925 --> 00:11:29,566
You know, Peyton, one of these days you're gonna grow up

179
00:11:29,937 --> 00:11:32,488
and you won't have all the answers.

180
00:11:33,328 --> 00:11:36,517
You weren't even 10 years old when Ellie showed up.

181
00:11:36,568 --> 00:11:40,137
She had a drug habit, she moved around a lot.

182
00:11:40,203 --> 00:11:42,149
It wasn't even a year after your mother had died

183
00:11:42,195 --> 00:11:45,706
and  you were in a pretty rough place emotionally.

184
00:11:46,681 --> 00:11:48,672
And if you ask me, you still are.

185
00:11:48,728 --> 00:11:50,505
And guess what? So am I.

186
00:11:51,971 --> 00:11:56,270
I could not risk exposing you to her.

187
00:11:56,342 --> 00:11:58,871
No way -- not then.

188
00:11:59,471 --> 00:12:01,882
Fine! Fine -- not then.

189
00:12:01,938 --> 00:12:06,383
Okay, but what about sometime in, oh, I don't know, the last eight years?

190
00:12:06,765 --> 00:12:07,953
What about then?

191
00:12:08,554 --> 00:12:10,996
Or, like, what about now?

192
00:12:11,071 --> 00:12:13,514
I suppose now is up to you.

193
00:12:33,888 --> 00:12:34,906
Hey, you.

194
00:12:35,332 --> 00:12:36,617
"Hey" back at you.

195
00:12:37,189 --> 00:12:40,830
1972's outside. It wants its furniture back.

196
00:12:40,918 --> 00:12:43,073
You mock, but you don't know.

197
00:12:43,155 --> 00:12:44,398
Try out the couch.

198
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:51,039
Nice.

199
00:12:51,324 --> 00:12:53,487
No, I said...

200
00:12:55,301 --> 00:12:57,223
try out the couch.

201
00:13:03,690 --> 00:13:04,945
I like this couch.

202
00:13:05,016 --> 00:13:06,522
I thought you would.

203
00:13:08,186 --> 00:13:12,003
Oh, way too early in the day for me to see this.

204
00:13:12,544 --> 00:13:14,915
Well, what hour would you prefer to watch us?

205
00:13:14,991 --> 00:13:17,397
Oh, how about never o'clock?

206
00:13:17,469 --> 00:13:19,854
Or maybe, uh, I don't know, quarter after stab out my eyes?

207
00:13:19,901 --> 00:13:21,345
Either one's really good for me.

208
00:13:21,575 --> 00:13:24,063
By the way, that couch has not been staingarded yet.

209
00:13:24,115 --> 00:13:25,867
You may want to get a room instead.

210
00:13:25,933 --> 00:13:29,419
Well, if we get a room, then you're gonna be stuck on this tiny couch.

211
00:13:29,762 --> 00:13:31,032
That's a good point.

212
00:13:32,337 --> 00:13:34,171
Give me a minute. We'll go to the beach.

213
00:13:41,594 --> 00:13:43,089
Brooke asked me to help her out.

214
00:13:43,161 --> 00:13:45,998
And by "Brooke," you mean your part-time girlfriend Brooke?

215
00:13:46,905 --> 00:13:47,522
Yeah.

216
00:13:47,999 --> 00:13:49,626
We're gonna set up for the end-of-summer thing.

217
00:13:50,509 --> 00:13:52,245
What's  up with that, anyway?

218
00:13:52,752 --> 00:13:56,176
Well, you see, there's a season called "summer," Haley.

219
00:13:56,237 --> 00:13:59,208
And when that ends, another season called "fall" starts right up.

220
00:13:59,279 --> 00:14:03,103
Oh okay. Rephrasing -- what's up with the part-time girlfriend stuff?

221
00:14:03,564 --> 00:14:04,982
I don't know yet.

222
00:14:05,777 --> 00:14:07,467
Right now, we're on Brooke's terms.

223
00:14:08,098 --> 00:14:09,642
But I'll keep you posted.

224
00:14:09,719 --> 00:14:10,917
Oh, gee, thanks.

225
00:14:10,993 --> 00:14:12,786
I also came to check on you.

226
00:14:12,808 --> 00:14:14,029
I was worried about you.

227
00:14:14,117 --> 00:14:17,086
Nathan was in a pretty bad mood this morning at the river court.

228
00:14:17,435 --> 00:14:19,723
I thought that might have something to do with you.

229
00:14:21,812 --> 00:14:23,272
Nathan's home?

230
00:14:24,705 --> 00:14:27,777
You... didn't know he was back?

231
00:14:29,636 --> 00:14:30,460
No.

232
00:14:31,919 --> 00:14:32,974
No,  I didn't.

233
00:14:33,583 --> 00:14:35,381
I'm sorry, Haley.

234
00:14:35,626 --> 00:14:36,886
I thought you knew.

235
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:42,015
Can you just, um, tell Brooke that I'll see her tonight?

236
00:15:00,111 --> 00:15:03,470
Well, well. If it isn't my beloved daughter-in-law.

237
00:15:05,175 --> 00:15:08,953
Haley, it's so nice of you to come by and check on me following my accident.

238
00:15:09,065 --> 00:15:11,512
Oh, by the way, I think I found a pair of your black gloves.

239
00:15:11,599 --> 00:15:12,404
Leather, right?

240
00:15:12,435 --> 00:15:15,450
Uh, no, I-I don't own any black gloves, Mr. Scott.

241
00:15:16,347 --> 00:15:19,878
I know your parents aren't around, so call me "dad."

242
00:15:20,739 --> 00:15:23,048
I'd really just like to see Nathan.

243
00:15:23,488 --> 00:15:25,470
He didn't tell you he was coming home.

244
00:15:28,164 --> 00:15:30,427
Sometimes I'm so proud of that kid.

245
00:15:31,122 --> 00:15:32,484
Can I fix you a drink?

246
00:15:33,467 --> 00:15:35,945
I hear you rock stars are big drinkers, right?

247
00:15:37,365 --> 00:15:40,057
Well... suit yourself.

248
00:15:41,491 --> 00:15:43,353
Deb said you moved out.

249
00:15:43,456 --> 00:15:44,787
Yeah. It sucks, huh?

250
00:15:46,185 --> 00:15:47,373
My marriage is over.

251
00:15:48,325 --> 00:15:51,260
Who knew you and I would have so much in common, after all?

252
00:15:51,321 --> 00:15:53,394
Could you please just tell Nathan that I'm here?

253
00:15:53,456 --> 00:15:54,823
Oh, he's not home.

254
00:16:07,588 --> 00:16:08,857
