508
00:35:26,039 --> 00:35:27,201
Hey, girly.

509
00:35:28,675 --> 00:35:31,732
I left you like a million messages. Where have you been?

510
00:35:33,384 --> 00:35:34,225
Around.

511
00:35:42,782 --> 00:35:46,739
Drinking, huh? I should probably join you, with the night I'm having.

512
00:35:46,825 --> 00:35:50,144
It's like, Tim wants me to play, Nathan won't even talk to me.

513
00:35:50,231 --> 00:35:52,421
Well, it's not like you don't deserve it.

514
00:36:02,197 --> 00:36:03,235
Hey.

515
00:36:04,110 --> 00:36:05,068
Can I talk to you?

516
00:36:13,118 --> 00:36:14,498
I wanted to say I'm sorry.

517
00:36:14,888 --> 00:36:16,680
I should have told you I was back in town.

518
00:36:18,257 --> 00:36:19,182
It's okay.

519
00:36:20,002 --> 00:36:21,094
Not really.

520
00:36:22,839 --> 00:36:26,659
Look, I've been avoiding you because I'm still mad, Haley, about everything.

521
00:36:27,530 --> 00:36:30,001
I don't see that changing anytime soon.

522
00:36:33,883 --> 00:36:36,228
Do you know the last two times I came to the beach?

523
00:36:37,285 --> 00:36:40,089
For our wedding and to burn the wedding wall.

524
00:36:41,799 --> 00:36:43,571
So that's what happened to it.

525
00:36:44,046 --> 00:36:47,595
Well, first I broke it in half with the keyboard I bought you, and then I burned it.

526
00:36:48,457 --> 00:36:49,331
Sorry.

527
00:36:51,353 --> 00:36:56,950
Nathan, I need to ask you something, and I really don't want you to take it the wrong way, but...

528
00:36:58,208 --> 00:37:02,166
I need to know what you want from me or from us.

529
00:37:04,148 --> 00:37:05,321
What are we now?

530
00:37:06,652 --> 00:37:07,727
I don't know.

531
00:37:10,210 --> 00:37:11,890
What do you want us to be?

532
00:37:12,058 --> 00:37:14,757
I don't know, Haley. I can't answer that right now.

533
00:37:14,828 --> 00:37:15,781
I can.

534
00:37:16,599 --> 00:37:17,830
I want us to be together.

535
00:37:17,916 --> 00:37:18,934
Why?

536
00:37:20,097 --> 00:37:23,783
I mean, we're so far away from who we used to be. Why even fight for it?

537
00:37:23,855 --> 00:37:25,178
Because I love you.

538
00:37:29,103 --> 00:37:30,255
Listen...

539
00:37:31,561 --> 00:37:33,844
Basketball season's coming up and I'm --

540
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:35,538
I'm gonna concentrate on that.

541
00:37:35,555 --> 00:37:38,320
So you should do your thing, whatever it is --

542
00:37:38,421 --> 00:37:40,162
school, music --

543
00:37:40,387 --> 00:37:42,056
something other than me.

544
00:37:44,115 --> 00:37:47,683
Because I really don't know when I'm gonna be ready for us again...

545
00:37:48,129 --> 00:37:50,457
or even if I'll be ready for us at all.

546
00:37:50,489 --> 00:37:52,051
Nathan, don't say that. God --

547
00:37:52,138 --> 00:37:56,340
Haley, i'm not saying it to be mean, okay? I don't --

548
00:37:56,581 --> 00:37:58,630
I don't like hurting you.

549
00:37:58,937 --> 00:38:01,155
I'm just trying to be honest.

550
00:38:07,340 --> 00:38:09,329
I'm gonna head back.

551
00:38:16,117 --> 00:38:17,671
Nathan...

552
00:38:22,654 --> 00:38:24,435
I'm not going anywhere.

553
00:38:27,548 --> 00:38:28,532
Okay.

554
00:38:53,229 --> 00:38:54,638
And then...

555
00:38:55,432 --> 00:38:56,968
... there were two.

556
00:38:59,763 --> 00:39:01,463
That's not so bad.

557
00:39:02,226 --> 00:39:05,707
This is how we started last school year, and look how good that turned out.

558
00:39:11,217 --> 00:39:12,400
Let's take a walk.

559
00:39:24,652 --> 00:39:25,727
Give me a minute.

560
00:39:33,171 --> 00:39:34,719
What's going on, guys?

561
00:39:34,741 --> 00:39:35,674
What's up?

562
00:39:35,881 --> 00:39:37,194
You got a second?

563
00:39:37,281 --> 00:39:38,990
Sure. What's up?

564
00:39:40,597 --> 00:39:42,699
I'm the guy for you.

565
00:39:43,002 --> 00:39:44,978
I know we're just part-time, and that's cool.

566
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:47,252
You know, do whatever, have your fun.

567
00:39:48,104 --> 00:39:50,631
But one of these nights, you're gonna realize it.

568
00:39:51,515 --> 00:39:53,991
I'm the guy for you, Brooke Davis.

569
00:39:59,032 --> 00:39:59,998
You'll see.

570
00:40:04,137 --> 00:40:05,730
You guys take it easy.

571
00:40:43,127 --> 00:40:44,001
Here.

572
00:40:44,244 --> 00:40:45,876
It used to be my cocaine vial.

573
00:40:47,331 --> 00:40:50,469
I thought you might like it, considering you were buying drugs today.

574
00:41:06,263 --> 00:41:08,204
It's gonna be okay, Hales.

575
00:41:08,405 --> 00:41:14,124
As a matter of fact, I think that this is the beginning of a beautiful friendship...

576
00:41:15,153 --> 00:41:16,270
again.

